                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1767</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-10T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1917, 7 p.m</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 5, 5 p.m. Minister of Finance informs me Japanese inquired of Dr. Koo
                    as to the nature of Abbott’s visit to China. Lie stated that it was for the
                    purpose of information. No other enquiry is known.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
